A Pinterest website that allows sellers to use the API to manage their products. This will include real-time updates on metadata, higher checkout propensity, improved quality of data, and the ability to utilize features to scale shopping advertisements.
This will contain the data on when shoppers are most active. Sellers will also be able to see their total impact and presence on Pinterest, so they can further improve their performance. They can also update the items in their catalogs, whether an item is no longer available or they added a new product. 
This website will secure any sort of sensitive information, such as passwords and phone numbers. 
For functionality, this website will have a login/logout for sellers. A button under their page to update, create, delete, or view products. There will also be a button to get ad analytics and audience insights. 
